title: Low Prevalence of Anemia Among Women
description: In 2019, only 7.4% of women aged 15-49 in Guatemala were affected by anemia, indicating a relatively low prevalence compared to global averages.

title: Low Anemia Rates Among Non-Pregnant Women
description: Guatemala reported a low anemia prevalence of 7% among non-pregnant women aged 15-49 in 2019, showcasing a positive health indicator for women.

title: High Child Employment in Manufacturing
description: In 2015, 22.94% of economically active female children aged 7-14 were employed in manufacturing, highlighting a significant challenge in child labor.
